                            <comment id="12693832" author="gsingers" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2009 17:43:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I should also note this is probably more noticeable in this particular case due to the fact that the data in question has a lot of small fields.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12693835" author="gsingers" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2009 17:48:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-663&quot; title=&quot;Allow multiple files for stopwords, protwords and synonyms&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-663&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-663&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced the problem&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12693845" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2009 18:04:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Nice catch! Looks like KeepWordFilterFactory should also pass a CharArraySet, and then KeepWordFilter should check the set type, just like StopFilter does.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12694279" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 31 Mar 2009 22:21:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch to fix this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adds tests&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Simplifies the inform code (fixing another issue related to the original code)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fixes the performance problem&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fixes a small performance problem on the KeepFilter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
